
1) Download the guide

svn co https://root.cern.ch/svn/root/branches/dev/roostats/roofit/roostats/doc/usersguide/


2) Install dot2tex

Download the package from http://www.fauskes.net/code/dot2tex/download/.

Make a new directory where you install the python modules (locally)

mkdir <py_dest_dir>
(in my case: mkdir ~/public/RooStats/python)

Unpack the dot2tex file and then inside do:

python setup.py install --home=<py_dest_dir>
(in my case: python setup.py install --home=~/public/RooStats/python)

Check if inside <py_dest_dir> you have bin and lib directories.


3) Install pyparsing

Download from http://pyparsing.wikispaces.com/

Unpack and then inside do:

python setup.py install --home=<py_dest_dir>
(NOTE home it is the same directory as before)
(in my case: python setup.py install --home=~/public/RooStats/python)

I got an error, but it seems to work in any case...

