---


4) Set the python search directory for the modules:

export PYTHONPATH=<py_dest_dir>/lib/python:$PYTHONHOME
(in my case: export PYTHONPATH=~/public/RooStats/python/lib/python:$PYTHONHOME)

and add in the path the bin directory:

export PATH=$PATH:<py_dest_dir>/bin
(in my case export PATH=$PATH:~/public/RooStats/python/bin)


5) In lxplus there is an old version of the latex package: xkeyval

You need to update it.

Download it from http://ctan.org/tex-archive/macros/latex/contrib/xkeyval/.

wget http://mirror.ctan.org/macros/latex/contrib/xkeyval.zip

Unpack it and the copy the files  xkeyval/run/xkeyval.* (.sty and .tex) inside the usersguide directory.


6) Then it is missing the module: tikz

http://www.texample.net/tikz/

wget http://media.texample.net/pgf/builds/pgfCVS2010-03-28_TDS.zip

Unpack it (it produces a directory tex) and then make a new directory in your home:

mkdir ~/texmf

Inside this directory make a symbolic link:

ln -s <where is the package>/tex


7) You need to install preview for latex:

wget http://mirror.ctan.org/macros/latex/contrib/preview.zip

Unzip it and then inside do:

tex preview.ins

It produces a lot of files. 
Make those files visible to latex, just making a symbolic link inside 
the texmf directory in your home. 
Go inside ~/texmf/tex/generic and then do

ln -s <where is preview>/preview
(in my case ln -s ~/public/RooStats/preview)


8) Now you can run!

NOTE: everytime you open the shell you need JUST to set the env variables:

export PYTHONPATH=~/public/RooStats/python/lib/python:$PYTHONHOME
export PATH=$PATH:~/public/RooStats/python/bin

--- GS: on C-shell
setenv PYTHONPATH python/lib/python:$PYTHONHOME
setenv PATH ${PATH}:python/bin
---

You can put them in the shell profile file.

NOTE2: The files of the package xkeyval (point 5 of this guide) 
can be added inside texmf, removing them from the usersguide directory 
(in this way you don't need to add other files than the files in svn)

To do that, just make a symbolic link inside ~/texmf/tex/generic:

ln -s <where is xkeyval>/xkeyval
(in my case ln -s ~/public/RooStats/xkeyval)

and then inside ~/texmf/tex/latex:

ln -s <where is xkeyval>/xkeyval
(in my case ln -s ~/public/RooStats/xkeyval)


